cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY 

The paper deals with adapting information access provided by ubiquitous systems to users, which is a human-computer interaction (HCI) problem. Therefore, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with adapting the system to the user's social group, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
